CTRL - h , to delete back one char at the time in insert mode  ""USE THIS INSTEAD OF DAMN BACKSPACE""
CTRL - w , to delete back one word
CTRL - u , to delete to start of line

CTRL - o , to enter insert normal mode ""Will enter normal mode and then after one command it will go back to insert""

CTRL - r {register} for pasting stuff from insert mode.
CTRL - r CTRL - p {register} inserts text and fixes any unitended indentation.
CTRL - r = for in place calculations.
CTRL - v {code} turn any arbitrary char to its numeric code





